Preparation of preschool and class teachers for teaching physical education as a subject. Theoretical knowledge on basic study-organizational aspects of physical education classes and the effect of exercise on the organism proceeding from individual features.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to prepare preschool and class teachers for teaching physical education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1.Student knows the principles how to organize PE lesson, teaching methods and teachers` role in lesson. 2.Student understand the difference between the main motor skills and physical fitness. 3.Student knows how to choose a moving game in accordance with the purpose. 4.Student is able to compose a PE lesson plan. 5.Student can create correlation between PE activities and other subjects. 6.Student knows the principles how to plan the activities, aims, contents, and evaluation.   7.Students knows the difference of  lessons - training and teaching lesson.
